  "prompt": "What is the platform in which Facebook is built?",
  "response": "Facebook was originally built using PHP, a server-side scripting language designed for web development. Over time, Facebook's architecture has evolved, incorporating various technologies to support its massive scale and efficiency. The company introduced HipHop for PHP (HPHPc), later replaced by the HipHop Virtual Machine (HHVM), which significantly improves PHP performance. Additionally, Facebook uses other technologies and languages like JavaScript (including frameworks like React), Python, C++, and numerous backend infrastructure tools to manage its services.\n\nThe overall platform consists of a complex, multi-layered architecture that includes various databases, caching systems, and distributed computing tools to ensure scalability and reliability.",
